article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- — Corey Washington had 29 points to propel Saint Peter's to a 75-53 romp over Siena on Friday night. Washington had six rebounds for the Peacocks (12-11, 8-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Michael Houge finished with 10 points and 10 rebounds. Armoni Zeigler scored nine. Michael Ojo led the Saints (4-21, 3-11) with 13 points and four steals. Zek Tekin added nine points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
